<br>
I am not sure why someone I do not know would ask me to power-level them, but there you go. Comes with being a level 63 druid.<br>
<br>
So: I tell them, my time is valuable. I have a limited amount of time, and thus, when I spend time with them, I am not able to spend it with my friends and people I wish to actually converse with and have a good time with. So: You may pay me 10k pp per hour that I spend with you, power-leveling you. I think this is only fair. Especially since I have to put up with some begger who can't even be bothered to go level himself up or make friends with someone of a suitably high level who would want to PL them just because they like them. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
